# Zero Hardcoded Events Rule

This is the single most important architectural rule in Viridian Football.

## The Rule

Every interesting thing that happens must be the result of dynamic systems interacting through the event bus. Never hardcode events, storylines, or player-specific behaviors.

## Violations

- Checking a specific player name, team name, or season number to trigger behavior
- Writing `if (player.position === 'QB')` to trigger a narrative event
- Creating "story templates" that assume a specific context
- Hard-coding personality events for specific scenarios

## Correct Approach

All events fire based on **conditions**: thresholds, probabilities, and trait combinations.

```typescript
// BAD — checks identity
if (player.name === 'Star WR') triggerHoldout();

// GOOD — checks conditions that any player could meet
if (player.personality.ego > 80 && contract.isUnderpaid && stats.breakoutSeason) {
  bus.emit('HOLDOUT_INITIATED', { playerId: player.id, ... });
}
```

Every behavior must be reproducible by a different player/team under the same conditions.
